52Operand StackArgumentsAccessor::GetArgumentOperand(int index) const {
53 DCHECK_GE(index, 0);
54 // arg[0] = rsp + kPCOnStackSize;
55 // arg[i] = arg[0] + i * kSystemPointerSize;
56 return Operand(rsp, kPCOnStackSize + index * kSystemPointerSize);
57}

63void MacroAssembler::Load(Register destination, ExternalReference source) {
64 if (root_array_available_ && options().enable_root_relative_access) {
65 intptr_t delta = RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), source);
66 if (is_int32(delta)) {
67 movq(destination, Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta)));
68 return;
69 }
70 }
71 // Safe code.
72 if (destination == rax && !options().isolate_independent_code) {
73 load_rax(source);
74 } else {
75 movq(destination, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(source));
76 }
77}
78
79void MacroAssembler::Store(ExternalReference destination, Register source) {
80 if (root_array_available_ && options().enable_root_relative_access) {
81 intptr_t delta =
82 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), destination);
83 if (is_int32(delta)) {
84 movq(Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta)), source);
85 return;
86 }
87 }
88 // Safe code.
89 if (source == rax && !options().isolate_independent_code) {
90 store_rax(destination);
91 } else {
92 movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(destination), source);
93 }
94}

123void MacroAssembler::LoadAddress(Register destination,
124 ExternalReference source) {
125 if (root_array_available()) {
126 if (source.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
127 leaq(destination,
128 Operand(kRootRegister, source.offset_from_root_register()));
129 return;
130 }
131 if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
132 intptr_t delta =
133 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), source);
134 if (is_int32(delta)) {
135 leaq(destination, Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta)));
136 return;
137 }
138 } else if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
139 IndirectLoadExternalReference(destination, source);
140 return;
141 }
142 }
143 Move(destination, source);
144}
145
146Operand MacroAssembler::ExternalReferenceAsOperand(ExternalReference reference,
147 Register scratch) {
148 if (root_array_available()) {
149 if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
150 return Operand(kRootRegister, reference.offset_from_root_register());
151 }
152 if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
153 int64_t delta =
154 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
155 if (is_int32(delta)) {
156 return Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(delta));
157 }
158 }
159 if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
160 if (IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(), reference)) {
161 // Some external references can be efficiently loaded as an offset from
162 // kRootRegister.
163 intptr_t offset =
164 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
165 CHECK(is_int32(offset));
166 return Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
167 } else {
168 // Otherwise, do a memory load from the external reference table.
169 movq(scratch, Operand(kRootRegister,
170 RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReferenceTableEntry(
171 isolate(), reference)));
172 return Operand(scratch, 0);
173 }
174 }
175 }
176 Move(scratch, reference);
177 return Operand(scratch, 0);
178}

190void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
191 static_assert(!CanBeImmediate(RootIndex::kUndefinedValue) ||
192 std::is_same_v<Tagged_t, uint32_t>);
193 if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
194 mov_tagged(destination,
195 Immediate(static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))));
196 return;
197 }
198 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
199 movq(destination, RootAsOperand(index));
200}

202void MacroAssembler::LoadRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
203 if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
204 DecompressTagged(destination,
205 static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index)));
206 return;
207 }
208 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
209 movq(destination, RootAsOperand(index));
210}

212void MacroAssembler::PushRoot(RootIndex index) {
213 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
214 Push(RootAsOperand(index));
215}

217void MacroAssembler::CompareRoot(Register with, RootIndex index,
218 ComparisonMode mode) {
219 if (mode == ComparisonMode::kFullPointer ||
220 !base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
221 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
222 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
223 cmpq(with, RootAsOperand(index));
224 return;
225 }
226 CompareTaggedRoot(with, index);
227}
228
229void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRoot(Register with, RootIndex index) {
230 AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(with);
231 if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
232 cmp_tagged(with, Immediate(static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))));
233 return;
234 }
235 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
236 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
237 DCHECK(base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
238 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot));
239 cmp_tagged(with, RootAsOperand(index));
240}
241
242void MacroAssembler::CompareRoot(Operand with, RootIndex index) {
243 if (CanBeImmediate(index)) {
244 cmp_tagged(with, Immediate(static_cast<uint32_t>(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))));
245 return;
246 }
247 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
248 DCHECK(!with.AddressUsesRegister(kScratchRegister));
249 if (base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
250 RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
251 mov_tagged(kScratchRegister, RootAsOperand(index));
252 cmp_tagged(with, kScratchRegister);
253 } else {
254 // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
255 movq(kScratchRegister, RootAsOperand(index));
256 cmpq(with, kScratchRegister);
257 }
258}

272void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
273 Label* fbv_undef,
274 Label::Distance distance) {
275 Label done;
276
277 // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
278 TaggedRegister feedback_cell(dst);
279 LoadTaggedField(feedback_cell,
280 FieldOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
281 LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldOperand(feedback_cell, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
282
283 // Check if feedback vector is valid.
284 IsObjectType(dst, FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE, rcx);
285 j(equal, &done, Label::kNear);
286
287 // Not valid, load undefined.
288 LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
289 jmp(fbv_undef, distance);
290
291 bind(&done);
292}

315 // Clear the top two bytes (which may include metadata). Must be in sync with
316 // MapWord::Unpack, and vice versa.

428void MacroAssembler::RecordWriteField(Register object, int offset,
429 Register value, Register slot_address,
430 SaveFPRegsMode save_fp,
431 SmiCheck smi_check,
432 ReadOnlyCheck ro_check,
433 SlotDescriptor slot) {
434 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
435 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, slot_address));
436 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
437 // catch stores of Smis and read-only objects.
438 Label done;
439
440#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
441 if (ro_check == ReadOnlyCheck::kInline) {
442 // Quick check for Read-only and small Smi values.
443 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kLastAllocatedRoot < kRegularPageSize);
444 JumpIfUnsignedLessThan(value, kRegularPageSize, &done);
445 }
446#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
447
448 // Skip barrier if writing a smi.
449 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
450 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
451 }
452
453 // Although the object register is tagged, the offset is relative to the start
454 // of the object, so the offset must be a multiple of kTaggedSize.
455 DCHECK(IsAligned(offset, kTaggedSize));
456
457 leaq(slot_address, FieldOperand(object, offset));
458 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
459 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Debug check slot_address");
460 Label ok;
461 testb(slot_address, Immediate(kTaggedSize - 1));
462 j(zero, &ok, Label::kNear);
463 int3();
464 bind(&ok);
465 }
466
467 RecordWrite(object, slot_address, value, save_fp, SmiCheck::kOmit,
468 ReadOnlyCheck::kOmit, slot);
469
470 bind(&done);
471
472 // Clobber clobbered input registers when running with the debug-code flag
473 // turned on to provoke errors.
474 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
475 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Zap scratch registers");
476 Move(value, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
477 Move(slot_address, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
478 }
479}

518void MacroAssembler::LoadExternalPointerField(
519 Register destination, Operand field_operand,
520 ExternalPointerTagRange tag_range, Register scratch,
521 IsolateRootLocation isolateRootLocation) {
522 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
523#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
524 DCHECK(!tag_range.IsEmpty());
525 DCHECK(!IsSharedExternalPointerType(tag_range));
526 DCHECK(!field_operand.AddressUsesRegister(scratch));
527 if (isolateRootLocation == IsolateRootLocation::kInRootRegister) {
528 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
529 // TODO(saelo): consider using an ExternalReference here.
530 movq(scratch,
531 Operand(kRootRegister,
532 IsolateData::external_pointer_table_offset() +
533 Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset));
534 } else {
535 DCHECK(isolateRootLocation == IsolateRootLocation::kInScratchRegister);
536 movq(scratch,
537 Operand(scratch,
538 IsolateData::external_pointer_table_offset() +
539 Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset));
540 }
541 movl(destination, field_operand);
542 shrq(destination, Immediate(kExternalPointerIndexShift));
543 static_assert(kExternalPointerTableEntrySize == 8);
544 movq(destination, Operand(scratch, destination, times_8, 0));
545
546 // We don't expect to see empty fields here. If this is ever needed, consider
547 // using an dedicated empty value entry for those tags instead (i.e. an entry
548 // with the right tag and nullptr payload).
549 DCHECK(!ExternalPointerCanBeEmpty(tag_range));
550
551 if (tag_range.Size() == 1) {
552 // The common and simple case: we expect exactly one tag.
553 movq(scratch, destination);
554 shrq(scratch, Immediate(kExternalPointerTagShift));
555 andl(scratch, Immediate(kExternalPointerShiftedTagMask));
556 cmpl(scratch, Immediate(tag_range.first));
557 SbxCheck(equal, AbortReason::kExternalPointerTagMismatch);
558 movq(scratch, Immediate64(kExternalPointerPayloadMask));
559 andq(destination, scratch);
560 } else {
561 // Not currently supported. Implement once needed.
562 DCHECK_NE(tag_range, kAnyExternalPointerTagRange);
563 UNREACHABLE();
564 }
565#else
566 movq(destination, field_operand);
567#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
568}

615#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
616void MacroAssembler::ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(Register destination,
617 Register handle,
618 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
619 // The tag implies which pointer table to use.
620 if (tag == kUnknownIndirectPointerTag) {
621 // In this case we have to rely on the handle marking to determine which
622 // pointer table to use.
623 Label is_trusted_pointer_handle, done;
624 testl(handle, Immediate(kCodePointerHandleMarker));
625 j(zero, &is_trusted_pointer_handle, Label::kNear);
626 ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
627 jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
628 bind(&is_trusted_pointer_handle);
629 ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle,
630 kUnknownIndirectPointerTag);
631 bind(&done);
632 } else if (tag == kCodeIndirectPointerTag) {
633 ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
634 } else {
635 ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
636 }
637}
638
639void MacroAssembler::ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(Register destination,
640 Register handle,
641 IndirectPointerTag tag) {
642 DCHECK_NE(tag, kCodeIndirectPointerTag);
643 DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
644 shrl(handle, Immediate(kTrustedPointerHandleShift));
645 static_assert(kTrustedPointerTableEntrySize == 8);
646 DCHECK(root_array_available_);
647 movq(destination,
648 Operand{kRootRegister, IsolateData::trusted_pointer_table_offset()});
649 movq(destination, Operand{destination, handle, times_8, 0});
650 // Untag the pointer and remove the marking bit in one operation.
651 Register tag_reg = handle;
652 movq(tag_reg, Immediate64(~(tag | kTrustedPointerTableMarkBit)));
653 andq(destination, tag_reg);
654}
655
656void MacroAssembler::ResolveCodePointerHandle(Register destination,
657 Register handle) {
658 DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
659 Register table = destination;
660 LoadAddress(table, ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_address());
661 shrl(handle, Immediate(kCodePointerHandleShift));
662 // The code pointer table entry size is 16 bytes, so we have to do an
663 // explicit shift first (times_16 doesn't exist).
664 shll(handle, Immediate(kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2));
665 movq(destination,
666 Operand(table, handle, times_1, kCodePointerTableEntryCodeObjectOffset));
667 // The LSB is used as marking bit by the code pointer table, so here we have
668 // to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
669 orq(destination, Immediate(kHeapObjectTag));
670}
671
672void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(Register destination,
673 Operand field_operand,
674 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
675 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, kScratchRegister));
676 DCHECK(!field_operand.AddressUsesRegister(kScratchRegister));
677 DCHECK_NE(tag, kInvalidEntrypointTag);
678 LoadAddress(kScratchRegister,
679 ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_address());
680 movl(destination, field_operand);
681 shrl(destination, Immediate(kCodePointerHandleShift));
682 shll(destination, Immediate(kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2));
683 movq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, destination, times_1, 0));
684 if (tag != 0) {
685 // Can this be improved?
686 movq(kScratchRegister, Immediate64(tag));
687 xorq(destination, kScratchRegister);
688 }
689}
690#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
691
692#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
693void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
694 Register destination, Register dispatch_handle) {
695 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, dispatch_handle, kScratchRegister));
696 LoadAddress(kScratchRegister, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
697 movq(destination, dispatch_handle);
698 shrl(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
699 shll(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
700 movq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, destination, times_1,
701 JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
702}
703
704void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
705 Register destination, JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle) {
706 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, kScratchRegister));
707 LoadAddress(kScratchRegister, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
708 // WARNING: This offset calculation is only safe if we have already stored a
709 // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle, e.g. in CallJSDispatchEntry, (thus
710 // keeping the dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not
711 // compatible (thus meaning that the offset calculation is not invalidated by
712 // a compaction).
713 // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
714 static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
715 int offset = JSDispatchTable::OffsetOfEntry(dispatch_handle) +
716 JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset;
717 movq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, offset));
718}

720void MacroAssembler::LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
721 Register destination, Register dispatch_handle) {
722 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, dispatch_handle, kScratchRegister));
723 LoadAddress(kScratchRegister, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
724 movq(destination, dispatch_handle);
725 shrl(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
726 shll(destination, Immediate(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
727 static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
728 movzxwq(destination, Operand(kScratchRegister, destination, times_1,
729 JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
730}
731
732void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
733 Register entrypoint, Register parameter_count, Register dispatch_handle) {
734 DCHECK(!AreAliased(entrypoint, parameter_count, dispatch_handle,
735 kScratchRegister));
736 LoadAddress(kScratchRegister, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
737 Register offset = parameter_count;
738 movq(offset, dispatch_handle);
739 shrl(offset, Immediate(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
740 shll(offset, Immediate(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
741 movq(entrypoint, Operand(kScratchRegister, offset, times_1,
742 JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
743 static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
744 movzxwq(parameter_count, Operand(kScratchRegister, offset, times_1,
745 JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
746}

915void MacroAssembler::RecordWrite(Register object, Register slot_address,
916 Register value, SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
917 SmiCheck smi_check, ReadOnlyCheck ro_check,
918 SlotDescriptor slot) {
919 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
920 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address, value));
921 AssertNotSmi(object);
922
923 if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
924 return;
925 }
926
927 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
928 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Debug check slot_address");
929 Label ok;
930 if (slot.contains_indirect_pointer()) {
931 Push(object); // Use object register as scratch
932 Register scratch = object;
933 Push(slot_address); // Use slot address register to load the value into
934 Register value_in_slot = slot_address;
935 LoadIndirectPointerField(value_in_slot, Operand(slot_address, 0),
936 slot.indirect_pointer_tag(), scratch);
937 cmp_tagged(value, value_in_slot);
938 // These pops don't affect the flag registers, so we can do them before
939 // the conditional jump below.
940 Pop(slot_address);
941 Pop(object);
942 } else {
943 cmp_tagged(value, Operand(slot_address, 0));
944 }
945 j(equal, &ok, Label::kNear);
946 int3();
947 bind(&ok);
948 }
949
950 // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
951 // catch stores of smis and read-only objects, as well as stores into the
952 // young generation.
953 Label done;
954
955#if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
956 if (ro_check == ReadOnlyCheck::kInline) {
957 // Quick check for Read-only and small Smi values.
958 static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kLastAllocatedRoot < kRegularPageSize);
959 JumpIfUnsignedLessThan(value, kRegularPageSize, &done);
960 }
961#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
962
963 if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
964 // Skip barrier if writing a smi.
965 JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
966 }
967
968 if (slot.contains_indirect_pointer()) {
969 // The indirect pointer write barrier is only enabled during marking.
970 JumpIfNotMarking(&done);
971 } else {
972#if V8_ENABLE_STICKY_MARK_BITS_BOOL
973 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kScratchRegister, object, slot_address, value));
974 Label stub_call;
975
976 JumpIfMarking(&stub_call);
977
978 // Save the slot_address in the xmm scratch register.
979 movq(kScratchDoubleReg, slot_address);
980 Register scratch0 = slot_address;
981 CheckMarkBit(object, kScratchRegister, scratch0, carry, &done);
982 CheckPageFlag(value, kScratchRegister, MemoryChunk::kIsInReadOnlyHeapMask,
983 not_zero, &done, Label::kFar);
984 CheckMarkBit(value, kScratchRegister, scratch0, carry, &done);
985 movq(slot_address, kScratchDoubleReg);
986 bind(&stub_call);
987#else // !V8_ENABLE_STICKY_MARK_BITS_BOOL
988 CheckPageFlag(value,
989 value, // Used as scratch.
990 MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, zero, &done,
991 Label::kNear);
992
993 CheckPageFlag(object,
994 value, // Used as scratch.
995 MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask, zero, &done,
996 Label::kNear);
997#endif // !V8_ENABLE_STICKY_MARK_BITS_BOOL
998 }
999
1000 if (slot.contains_direct_pointer()) {
1001 CallRecordWriteStub(object, slot_address, fp_mode,
1002 StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
1003 } else {
1004 DCHECK(slot.contains_indirect_pointer());
1005 CallIndirectPointerBarrier(object, slot_address, fp_mode,
1006 slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
1007 }
1008
1009 bind(&done);
1010
1011 // Clobber clobbered registers when running with the debug-code flag
1012 // turned on to provoke errors.
1013 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
1014 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, "Zap scratch registers");
1015 Move(slot_address, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
1016 Move(value, kZapValue, RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
1017 }
1018}

1020void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cc, AbortReason reason) {
1021 Label L;
1022 j(cc, &L, Label::kNear);
1023 Abort(reason);
1024 // Control will not return here.
1025 bind(&L);
1026}

1028void MacroAssembler::SbxCheck(Condition cc, AbortReason reason) {
1029 Check(cc, reason);
1030}
1031
1032void MacroAssembler::CheckStackAlignment() {
1033 int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
1034 int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
1035 if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
1036 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1037 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
1038 Label alignment_as_expected;
1039 testq(rsp, Immediate(frame_alignment_mask));
1040 j(zero, &alignment_as_expected, Label::kNear);
1041 // Abort if stack is not aligned.
1042 int3();
1043 bind(&alignment_as_expected);
1044 }
1045}
1046
1047void MacroAssembler::AlignStackPointer() {
1048 const int kFrameAlignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
1049 if (kFrameAlignment > 0) {
1050 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(kFrameAlignment));
1051 DCHECK(is_int8(kFrameAlignment));
1052 andq(rsp, Immediate(-kFrameAlignment));
1053 }
1054}
1055
1056void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
1057 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1058 if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
1059 const char* msg = GetAbortReason(reason);
1060 RecordComment("Abort message: ");
1061 RecordComment(msg);
1062 }
1063
1064 // Avoid emitting call to builtin if requested.
1065 if (trap_on_abort()) {
1066 int3();
1067 return;
1068 }
1069
1070 if (should_abort_hard()) {
1071 // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
1072 FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
1073 Move(kCArgRegs[0], static_cast<int>(reason));
1074 PrepareCallCFunction(1);
1075 LoadAddress(rax, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
1076 call(rax);
1077 return;
1078 }
1079
1080 Move(rdx, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
1081
1082 {
1083 // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
1084 // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
1085 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
1086 if (root_array_available()) {
1087 // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
1088 // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
1089 // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
1090 // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
1091 Call(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(Builtin::kAbort));
1092 } else {
1093 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
1094 }
1095 }
1096
1097 // Control will not return here.
1098 int3();
1099}

1101void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
1102 int num_arguments) {
1103 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1104 // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
1105 // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
1106 // expectation.
1107 CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
1108
1109 // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
1110 // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
1111 // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
1112 // smarter.
1113 Move(rax, num_arguments);
1114 LoadAddress(rbx, ExternalReference::Create(f));
1115
1116 bool switch_to_central = options().is_wasm;
1117 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central));
1118}
1119
1120void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
1121 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
1122 // -- rsp[0] : return address
1123 // -- rsp[8] : argument num_arguments - 1
1124 // ...
1125 // -- rsp[8 * num_arguments] : argument 0 (receiver)
1126 //
1127 // For runtime functions with variable arguments:
1128 // -- rax : number of arguments
1129 // -----------------------------------
1130 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1131 const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
1132 DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
1133 if (function->nargs >= 0) {
1134 Move(rax, function->nargs);
1135 }
1136 JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
1137}
1138
1139void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& ext,
1140 bool builtin_exit_frame) {
1141 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1142 // Set the entry point and jump to the C entry runtime stub.
1143 LoadAddress(rbx, ext);
1144 TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
1145}

1147namespace {
1148
1149#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1150// Only used when leaptiering is disabled.
1151void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
1152 Register optimized_code_entry, Register closure,
1153 Register scratch1, Register scratch2,
1154 JumpMode jump_mode) {
1155 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
1156 // rax : actual argument count
1157 // rdx : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
1158 // rsi : current context, used for the runtime call
1159 // rdi : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
1160 // -----------------------------------
1161 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
1162 DCHECK_EQ(closure, kJSFunctionRegister);
1163 DCHECK(!AreAliased(rax, rdx, closure, rsi, optimized_code_entry, scratch1,
1164 scratch2));
1165
1166 Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
1167
1168 // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
1169 // marker field.
1170 __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, &heal_optimized_code_slot);
1171
1172 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
1173 __ LoadCodePointerField(
1174 optimized_code_entry,
1175 FieldOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset), scratch1);
1176
1177 // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
1178 // runtime to clear it.
1179 __ AssertCode(optimized_code_entry);
1180 __ TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(optimized_code_entry);
1181 __ j(not_zero, &heal_optimized_code_slot);
1182
1183 // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
1184 // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
1185 __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, closure,
1186 scratch1, scratch2);
1187 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
1188 __ Move(rcx, optimized_code_entry);
1189 __ JumpCodeObject(rcx, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
1190
1191 // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
1192 // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
1193 // and re-enter the closure's code.
1194 __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
1195 __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot, jump_mode);
1196}
1197#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING

1215
1216void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
1217 Runtime::FunctionId function_id, JumpMode jump_mode) {
1218 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
1219 // -- rax : actual argument count (preserved for callee)
1220 // -- rdx : new target (preserved for callee)
1221 // -- rdi : target function (preserved for callee)
1222 // -- r15 : dispatch handle (preserved for callee)
1223 // -----------------------------------
1224 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1225 {
1226 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
1227 // Push a copy of the target function, the new target, the actual argument
1228 // count, and the dispatch handle.
1229 Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
1230 Push(kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister);
1231 SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1232 Push(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1233#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1234 // No need to SmiTag since dispatch handles always look like Smis.
1235 static_assert(kJSDispatchHandleShift > 0);
1236 Push(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
1237#endif
1238 // Function is also the parameter to the runtime call.
1239 Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
1240
1241 CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
1242 movq(rcx, rax);
1243
1244 // Restore target function, new target, actual argument count, and dispatch
1245 // handle.
1246#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1247 Pop(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
1248#endif
1249 Pop(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1250 SmiUntagUnsigned(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
1251 Pop(kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister);
1252 Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
1253 }
1254 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
1255 JumpCodeObject(rcx, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
1256}
1257
1258void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
1259 Register optimized_code, Register closure, Register scratch1,
1260 Register slot_address) {
1261 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1262 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure, scratch1, slot_address));
1263 DCHECK_EQ(closure, kJSFunctionRegister);
1264
1265#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1266 UNREACHABLE();
1267#else
1268 // Store the optimized code in the closure.
1269 AssertCode(optimized_code);
1270 StoreCodePointerField(FieldOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset),
1271 optimized_code);
1272
1273 // Write barrier clobbers scratch1 below.
1274 Register value = scratch1;
1275 movq(value, optimized_code);
1276
1277 RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, value, slot_address,
1278 SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore, SmiCheck::kOmit,
1279 ReadOnlyCheck::kOmit, SlotDescriptor::ForCodePointerSlot());
1280#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
1281}

1285// Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
1286// is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
1287Condition MacroAssembler::CheckFeedbackVectorFlagsNeedsProcessing(
1288 Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind) {
1289 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1290 DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
1291 uint32_t flag_mask =
1292 FeedbackVector::FlagMaskForNeedsProcessingCheckFrom(current_code_kind);
1293 testw(FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset),
1294 Immediate(flag_mask));
1295 return not_zero;
1296}
1297
1298void MacroAssembler::CheckFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
1299 Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
1300 Label* flags_need_processing) {
1301 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1302 j(CheckFeedbackVectorFlagsNeedsProcessing(feedback_vector, current_code_kind),
1303 flags_need_processing);
1304}
1305
1306void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
1307 Register feedback_vector, Register closure, JumpMode jump_mode) {
1308 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1309 DCHECK(!AreAliased(feedback_vector, closure));
1310
1311 Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
1312 // Check if optimized code is available.
1313 testw(FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset),
1314 Immediate(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
1315 j(zero, &maybe_needs_logging);
1316
1317 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized, jump_mode);
1318
1319 bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
1320 testw(FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset),
1321 Immediate(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
1322 j(zero, &maybe_has_optimized_code);
1323 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution, jump_mode);
1324
1325 bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
1326 Register optimized_code_entry = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
1327 LoadTaggedField(
1328 optimized_code_entry,
1329 FieldOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
1330 TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, closure, r9,
1331 WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(),
1332 jump_mode);
1333}

1337int MacroAssembler::RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
1338 Register exclusion) const {
1339 int bytes = 0;
1340 RegList saved_regs = kCallerSaved - exclusion;
1341 bytes += kSystemPointerSize * saved_regs.Count();
1342
1343 // R12 to r15 are callee save on all platforms.
1344 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
1345 bytes += kStackSavedSavedFPSize * kAllocatableDoubleRegisters.Count();
1346 }
1347
1348 return bytes;
1349}
1350
1351int MacroAssembler::PushCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
1352 Register exclusion) {
1353 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1354 int bytes = 0;
1355 bytes += PushAll(kCallerSaved - exclusion);
1356 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
1357 bytes += PushAll(kAllocatableDoubleRegisters);
1358 }
1359
1360 return bytes;
1361}
1362
1363int MacroAssembler::PopCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion) {
1364 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1365 int bytes = 0;
1366 if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
1367 bytes += PopAll(kAllocatableDoubleRegisters);
1368 }
1369 bytes += PopAll(kCallerSaved - exclusion);
1370
1371 return bytes;
1372}

1374int MacroAssembler::PushAll(RegList registers) {
1375 int bytes = 0;
1376 for (Register reg : registers) {
1377 pushq(reg);
1378 bytes += kSystemPointerSize;
1379 }
1380 return bytes;
1381}
1382
1383int MacroAssembler::PopAll(RegList registers) {
1384 int bytes = 0;
1385 for (Register reg : base::Reversed(registers)) {
1386 popq(reg);
1387 bytes += kSystemPointerSize;
1388 }
1389 return bytes;
1390}
1391
1392int MacroAssembler::PushAll(DoubleRegList registers, int stack_slot_size) {
1393 if (registers.is_empty()) return 0;
1394 const int delta = stack_slot_size * registers.Count();
1395 AllocateStackSpace(delta);
1396 int slot = 0;
1397 for (XMMRegister reg : registers) {
1398 if (stack_slot_size == kDoubleSize) {
1399 Movsd(Operand(rsp, slot), reg);
1400 } else {
1401 DCHECK_EQ(stack_slot_size, 2 * kDoubleSize);
1402 Movdqu(Operand(rsp, slot), reg);
1403 }
1404 slot += stack_slot_size;
1405 }
1406 DCHECK_EQ(slot, delta);
1407 return delta;
1408}
1409
1410int MacroAssembler::PopAll(DoubleRegList registers, int stack_slot_size) {
1411 if (registers.is_empty()) return 0;
1412 int slot = 0;
1413 for (XMMRegister reg : registers) {
1414 if (stack_slot_size == kDoubleSize) {
1415 Movsd(reg, Operand(rsp, slot));
1416 } else {
1417 DCHECK_EQ(stack_slot_size, 2 * kDoubleSize);
1418 Movdqu(reg, Operand(rsp, slot));
1419 }
1420 slot += stack_slot_size;
1421 }
1422 DCHECK_EQ(slot, stack_slot_size * registers.Count());
1423 addq(rsp, Immediate(slot));
1424 return slot;
1425}

1595void MacroAssembler::Cvtqui2ss(XMMRegister dst, Register src) {
1596 Label done;
1597 Cvtqsi2ss(dst, src);
1598 testq(src, src);
1599 j(positive, &done, Label::kNear);
1600
1601 // Compute {src/2 | (src&1)} (retain the LSB to avoid rounding errors).
1602 if (src != kScratchRegister) movq(kScratchRegister, src);
1603 shrq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(1));
1604 // The LSB is shifted into CF. If it is set, set the LSB in {tmp}.
1605 Label msb_not_set;
1606 j(not_carry, &msb_not_set, Label::kNear);
1607 orq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(1));
1608 bind(&msb_not_set);
1609 Cvtqsi2ss(dst, kScratchRegister);
1610 Addss(dst, dst);
1611 bind(&done);
1612}

1715void MacroAssembler::Cvtpd2ph(XMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src, Register tmp) {
1716 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1717 CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
1718 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
1719 Register tmp2 = kScratchRegister;
1720 DCHECK_NE(tmp, tmp2);
1721 DCHECK_NE(dst, src);
1722
1723 // Conversion algo from
1724 // https://github.com/tc39/proposal-float16array/issues/12#issuecomment-2256642971
1725 Label f32tof16;
1726 // Convert Float64 -> Float32.
1727 Cvtsd2ss(dst, src);
1728 vmovd(tmp, dst);
1729 // Mask off sign bit.
1730 andl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32WithoutSignMask));
1731 // Underflow to zero.
1732 cmpl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32MinFP16ZeroRepresentable));
1733 j(below, &f32tof16);
1734 // Overflow to infinity.
1735 cmpl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32MaxFP16Representable));
1736 j(above_equal, &f32tof16);
1737 // Detection of subnormal numbers.
1738 cmpl(tmp, Immediate(kFP32SubnormalThresholdOfFP16));
1739 setcc(above_equal, tmp2);
1740 movzxbl(tmp2, tmp2);
1741 // Compute 0x1000 for normal and 0x0000 for denormal numbers.
1742 shll(tmp2, Immediate(12));
1743 // Look at the last thirteen bits of the mantissa which will be shifted out
1744 // when converting from float32 to float16. (The round and sticky bits.)
1745 // Normal numbers: If the round bit is set and sticky bits are zero, then
1746 // adjust the float32 mantissa.
1747 // Denormal numbers: If all bits are zero, then adjust the mantissa.
1748 andl(tmp, Immediate(0x1fff));
1749 // Check round and sticky bits.
1750 cmpl(tmp, tmp2);
1751 j(not_equal, &f32tof16);
1752
1753 // Adjust mantissa by -1/0/+1.
1754 Move(kScratchDoubleReg, static_cast<uint32_t>(1));
1755 psignd(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1756 paddd(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1757
1758 bind(&f32tof16);
1759 // Convert Float32 -> Float16.
1760 vcvtps2ph(dst, dst, 4);
1761}

1763namespace {
1764template <typename OperandOrXMMRegister, bool is_double>
1765void ConvertFloatToUint64(MacroAssembler* masm, Register dst,
1766 OperandOrXMMRegister src, Label* fail) {
1767 Label success;
1768 // There does not exist a native float-to-uint instruction, so we have to use
1769 // a float-to-int, and postprocess the result.
1770 if (is_double) {
1771 masm->Cvttsd2siq(dst, src);
1772 } else {
1773 masm->Cvttss2siq(dst, src);
1774 }
1775 // If the result of the conversion is positive, we are already done.
1776 masm->testq(dst, dst);
1777 masm->j(positive, &success);
1778 // The result of the first conversion was negative, which means that the
1779 // input value was not within the positive int64 range. We subtract 2^63
1780 // and convert it again to see if it is within the uint64 range.
1781 if (is_double) {
1782 masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -9223372036854775808.0);
1783 masm->Addsd(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1784 masm->Cvttsd2siq(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1785 } else {
1786 masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -9223372036854775808.0f);
1787 masm->Addss(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1788 masm->Cvttss2siq(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1789 }
1790 masm->testq(dst, dst);
1791 // The only possible negative value here is 0x8000000000000000, which is
1792 // used on x64 to indicate an integer overflow.
1793 masm->j(negative, fail ? fail : &success);
1794 // The input value is within uint64 range and the second conversion worked
1795 // successfully, but we still have to undo the subtraction we did
1796 // earlier.
1797 masm->Move(kScratchRegister, 0x8000000000000000);
1798 masm->orq(dst, kScratchRegister);
1799 masm->bind(&success);
1800}
1801
1802template <typename OperandOrXMMRegister, bool is_double>
1803void ConvertFloatToUint32(MacroAssembler* masm, Register dst,
1804 OperandOrXMMRegister src, Label* fail) {
1805 Label success;
1806 // There does not exist a native float-to-uint instruction, so we have to use
1807 // a float-to-int, and postprocess the result.
1808 if (is_double) {
1809 masm->Cvttsd2si(dst, src);
1810 } else {
1811 masm->Cvttss2si(dst, src);
1812 }
1813 // If the result of the conversion is positive, we are already done.
1814 masm->testl(dst, dst);
1815 masm->j(positive, &success);
1816 // The result of the first conversion was negative, which means that the
1817 // input value was not within the positive int32 range. We subtract 2^31
1818 // and convert it again to see if it is within the uint32 range.
1819 if (is_double) {
1820 masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -2147483648.0);
1821 masm->Addsd(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1822 masm->Cvttsd2si(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1823 } else {
1824 masm->Move(kScratchDoubleReg, -2147483648.0f);
1825 masm->Addss(kScratchDoubleReg, src);
1826 masm->Cvttss2si(dst, kScratchDoubleReg);
1827 }
1828 masm->testl(dst, dst);
1829 // The only possible negative value here is 0x80000000, which is
1830 // used on x64 to indicate an integer overflow.
1831 masm->j(negative, fail ? fail : &success);
1832 // The input value is within uint32 range and the second conversion worked
1833 // successfully, but we still have to undo the subtraction we did
1834 // earlier.
1835 masm->Move(kScratchRegister, 0x80000000);
1836 masm->orl(dst, kScratchRegister);
1837 masm->bind(&success);
1838}

1932void MacroAssembler::I64x4Mul(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister lhs, YMMRegister rhs,
1933 YMMRegister tmp1, YMMRegister tmp2) {
1934 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
1935 DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, tmp1, tmp2));
1936 DCHECK(!AreAliased(lhs, tmp1, tmp2));
1937 DCHECK(!AreAliased(rhs, tmp1, tmp2));
1938 DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
1939 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX2);
1940 // 1. Multiply high dword of each qword of left with right.
1941 vpsrlq(tmp1, lhs, uint8_t{32});
1942 vpmuludq(tmp1, tmp1, rhs);
1943 // 2. Multiply high dword of each qword of right with left.
1944 vpsrlq(tmp2, rhs, uint8_t{32});
1945 vpmuludq(tmp2, tmp2, lhs);
1946 // 3. Add 1 and 2, then shift left by 32 (this is the high dword of result).
1947 vpaddq(tmp2, tmp2, tmp1);
1948 vpsllq(tmp2, tmp2, uint8_t{32});
1949 // 4. Multiply low dwords (this is the low dword of result).
1950 vpmuludq(dst, lhs, rhs);
1951 // 5. Add 3 and 4.
1952 vpaddq(dst, dst, tmp2);
1953}

2052void MacroAssembler::F16x8Min(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister lhs, XMMRegister rhs,
2053 YMMRegister scratch, YMMRegister scratch2) {
2054 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2055 CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2056 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2057 CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2058 vcvtph2ps(scratch, lhs);
2059 vcvtph2ps(scratch2, rhs);
2060 // The minps instruction doesn't propagate NaNs and +0's in its first
2061 // operand. Perform minps in both orders, merge the results, and adjust.
2062 vminps(dst, scratch, scratch2);
2063 vminps(scratch, scratch2, scratch);
2064 // Propagate -0's and NaNs, which may be non-canonical.
2065 vorps(scratch, scratch, dst);
2066 // Canonicalize NaNs by quieting and clearing the payload.
2067 vcmpunordps(dst, dst, scratch);
2068 vorps(scratch, scratch, dst);
2069 vpsrld(dst, dst, uint8_t{10});
2070 vandnps(dst, dst, scratch);
2071 vcvtps2ph(dst, dst, 0);

2074void MacroAssembler::F16x8Max(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister lhs, XMMRegister rhs,

2202void MacroAssembler::I32x8SConvertF32x8(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister src,
2203 YMMRegister tmp, Register scratch) {
2204 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2205 DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
2206 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2207 CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2208 Operand int32_overflow_as_float = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
2209 ExternalReference::address_of_wasm_i32x8_int32_overflow_as_float(),
2210 scratch);
2211 // This algorithm works by:
2212 // 1. lanes with NaNs are zero-ed
2213 // 2. lanes ge than 2147483648.0f (MAX_INT32+1) set to 0xffff'ffff
2214 // 3. cvttps2dq sets all out of range lanes to 0x8000'0000
2215 // a. correct for underflows (< MIN_INT32)
2216 // b. wrong for overflow, and we know which lanes overflow from 2.
2217 // 4. adjust for 3b by xor-ing 2 and 3
2218 // a. 0x8000'0000 xor 0xffff'ffff = 0x7fff'ffff (MAX_INT32)
2219 vcmpeqps(tmp, src, src);
2220 vandps(dst, src, tmp);
2221 vcmpgeps(tmp, src, int32_overflow_as_float);
2222 vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2223 vpxor(dst, dst, tmp);
2224}

2226void MacroAssembler::I16x8SConvertF16x8(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src,
2227 YMMRegister tmp, Register scratch) {
2228 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2229 DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2) &&
2230 CpuFeatures::IsSupported(F16C));
2231
2232 CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2233 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2234 CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2235
2236 Operand op = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
2237 ExternalReference::address_of_wasm_i32x8_int32_overflow_as_float(),
2238 scratch);
2239 // Convert source f16 to f32.
2240 vcvtph2ps(dst, src);
2241 // Compare it to itself, NaNs are turn to 0s because don't equal to itself.
2242 vcmpeqps(tmp, dst, dst);
2243 // Reset NaNs.
2244 vandps(dst, dst, tmp);
2245 // Detect positive Infinity as an overflow above MAX_INT32.
2246 vcmpgeps(tmp, dst, op);
2247 // Convert f32 to i32.
2248 vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2249 // cvttps2dq sets all out of range lanes to 0x8000'0000,
2250 // but as soon as source values are result of conversion from f16,
2251 // and so less than MAX_INT32, only +Infinity is an issue.
2252 // Convert all infinities to MAX_INT32 and let vpackssdw
2253 // clamp it to MAX_INT16 later.
2254 // 0x8000'0000 xor 0xffff'ffff(from 2 steps before) = 0x7fff'ffff (MAX_INT32)
2255 vpxor(dst, dst, tmp);
2256 // We now have 8 i32 values. Using one character per 16 bits:
2257 // dst: [AABBCCDDEEFFGGHH]
2258 // Create a copy of the upper four values in the lower half of {tmp}
2259 // (so the upper half of the immediate doesn't matter):
2260 vpermq(tmp, dst, 0x4E); // 0b01001110
2261 // tmp: [EEFFGGHHAABBCCDD]
2262 // Now pack them together as i16s. Note that {vpackssdw} interleaves
2263 // 128-bit chunks from each input, and takes care of saturating each
2264 // value to kMinInt16 and kMaxInt16. We will then ignore the upper half
2265 // of {dst}.
2266 vpackssdw(dst, dst, tmp);
2267 // dst: [EFGHABCDABCDEFGH]
2268 // <--><--><--><-->
2269 // â†‘ â†‘ â†‘ â””â”€â”€ from lower half of {dst}
2270 // â”‚ â”‚ â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ from lower half of {tmp}
2271 // â”‚ â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ from upper half of {dst} (ignored)
2272 // â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ from upper half of {tmp} (ignored)
2273}

2275void MacroAssembler::I16x8TruncF16x8U(YMMRegister dst, XMMRegister src,
2276 YMMRegister tmp) {
2277 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2278 DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2) &&
2279 CpuFeatures::IsSupported(F16C));
2280
2281 CpuFeatureScope f16c_scope(this, F16C);
2282 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2283 CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2284
2285 Operand op = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
2286 ExternalReference::address_of_wasm_i32x8_int32_overflow_as_float(),
2287 kScratchRegister);
2288 vcvtph2ps(dst, src);
2289 // NAN->0, negative->0.
2290 vpxor(tmp, tmp, tmp);
2291 vmaxps(dst, dst, tmp);
2292 // Detect positive Infinity as an overflow above MAX_INT32.
2293 vcmpgeps(tmp, dst, op);
2294 // Convert to int.
2295 vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2296 // cvttps2dq sets all out of range lanes to 0x8000'0000,
2297 // but as soon as source values are result of conversion from f16,
2298 // and so less than MAX_INT32, only +Infinity is an issue.
2299 // Convert all infinities to MAX_INT32 and let vpackusdw
2300 // clamp it to MAX_INT16 later.
2301 // 0x8000'0000 xor 0xffff'ffff(from 2 steps before) = 0x7fff'ffff (MAX_INT32)
2302 vpxor(dst, dst, tmp);
2303 // Move high part to a spare register.
2304 // See detailed comment in {I16x8SConvertF16x8} for how this works.
2305 vpermq(tmp, dst, 0x4E); // 0b01001110
2306 vpackusdw(dst, dst, tmp);
2307}

2383void MacroAssembler::I32x8DotI8x32I7x32AddS(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister src1,

2391 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX_VNNI_INT8)) {
2392 CpuFeatureScope avx_vnni_int8_scope(this, AVX_VNNI_INT8);
2393 vpdpbssd(dst, src2, src1);
2394 return;
2395 } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX_VNNI)) {
2396 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX_VNNI);
2397 vpdpbusd(dst, src2, src1);
2398 return;
2399 }
2400
2401 DCHECK_NE(scratch, splat_reg);
2402 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2403 CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2404 // splat_reg = i16x16.splat(1)
2405 vpcmpeqd(splat_reg, splat_reg, splat_reg);
2406 vpsrlw(splat_reg, splat_reg, uint8_t{15});
2407 vpmaddubsw(scratch, src2, src1);
2408 vpmaddwd(scratch, splat_reg, scratch);
2409 vpaddd(dst, src3, scratch);
2410}
2411
2412void MacroAssembler::I32x8TruncF32x8U(YMMRegister dst, YMMRegister src,
2413 YMMRegister scratch1,
2414 YMMRegister scratch2) {
2415 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2416 DCHECK(CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(AVX2));
2417 CpuFeatureScope avx_scope(this, AVX);
2418 CpuFeatureScope avx2_scope(this, AVX2);
2419
2420 // NAN->0, negative->0.
2421 vpxor(scratch1, scratch1, scratch1);
2422 vmaxps(dst, src, scratch1);
2423 // scratch1: float representation of max_signed.
2424 vpcmpeqd(scratch1, scratch1, scratch1);
2425 vpsrld(scratch1, scratch1, uint8_t{1}); // 0x7fffffff
2426 vcvtdq2ps(scratch1, scratch1); // 0x4f000000
2427 // scratch2: convert (src-max_signed).
2428 // Set positive overflow lanes to 0x7FFFFFFF.
2429 // Set negative lanes to 0.
2430 vsubps(scratch2, dst, scratch1);
2431
2432 vcmpleps(scratch1, scratch1, scratch2);
2433 vcvttps2dq(scratch2, scratch2);
2434 vpxor(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2435 vpxor(scratch1, scratch1, scratch1);
2436 vpmaxsd(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2437 // Convert to int. Overflow lanes above max_signed will be 0x80000000.
2438 vcvttps2dq(dst, dst);
2439 // Add (src-max_signed) for overflow lanes.
2440 vpaddd(dst, dst, scratch2);
2441}

2649void MacroAssembler::SmiAddConstant(Operand dst, Tagged<Smi> constant) {
2650 if (constant.value() != 0) {
2651 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
2652 addl(Operand(dst, kSmiShift / kBitsPerByte), Immediate(constant.value()));
2653 } else {
2654 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2655 if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) {
2656 // Sign-extend value after addition
2657 movl(kScratchRegister, dst);
2658 addl(kScratchRegister, Immediate(constant));
2659 movsxlq(kScratchRegister, kScratchRegister);
2660 movq(dst, kScratchRegister);
2661 } else {
2662 DCHECK_EQ(kTaggedSize, kInt32Size);
2663 addl(dst, Immediate(constant));
2664 }
2665 }
2666 }

2669SmiIndex MacroAssembler::SmiToIndex(Register dst, Register src, int shift) {
2670 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
2671 DCHECK(is_uint6(shift));
2672 // There is a possible optimization if shift is in the range 60-63, but that
2673 // will (and must) never happen.
2674 if (dst != src) {
2675 movq(dst, src);
2676 }
2677 if (shift < kSmiShift) {
2678 sarq(dst, Immediate(kSmiShift - shift));
2679 } else {
2680 shlq(dst, Immediate(shift - kSmiShift));
2681 }
2682 return SmiIndex(dst, times_1);
2683 } else {
2684 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
2685 // We have to sign extend the index register to 64-bit as the SMI might
2686 // be negative.
2687 movsxlq(dst, src);
2688 if (shift < kSmiShift) {
2689 sarq(dst, Immediate(kSmiShift - shift));
2690 } else if (shift != kSmiShift) {
2691 if (shift - kSmiShift <= static_cast<int>(times_8)) {
2692 return SmiIndex(dst, static_cast<ScaleFactor>(shift - kSmiShift));
2693 }
2694 shlq(dst, Immediate(shift - kSmiShift));
2695 }
2696 return SmiIndex(dst, times_1);
2697 }
2698}

2700void MacroAssembler::Switch(Register scratch, Register reg, int case_value_base,
2701 Label** labels, int num_labels) {
2702 Register table = scratch;
2703 Label fallthrough, jump_table;
2704 if (case_value_base != 0) {
2705 subq(reg, Immediate(case_value_base));
2706 }
2707 cmpq(reg, Immediate(num_labels));
2708 j(above_equal, &fallthrough);
2709 leaq(table, MemOperand(&jump_table));
2710#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CET_IBT
2711 // Add the notrack prefix to disable landing pad enforcement.
2712 jmp(MemOperand(table, reg, times_8, 0), /*notrack=*/true);
2713#else
2714 jmp(MemOperand(table, reg, times_8, 0));
2715#endif
2716 // Emit the jump table inline, under the assumption that it's not too big.
2717 Align(kSystemPointerSize);
2718 bind(&jump_table);
2719 for (int i = 0; i < num_labels; ++i) {
2720 dq(labels[i]);
2721 }
2722 bind(&fallthrough);
2723}
2724
2725void MacroAssembler::Push(Tagged<Smi> source) {
2726 intptr_t smi = static_cast<intptr_t>(source.ptr());
2727 if (is_int32(smi)) {
2728 Push(Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(smi)));
2729 return;
2730 }
2731 int first_byte_set = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros64(smi) / 8;
2732 int last_byte_set = (63 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(smi)) / 8;
2733 if (first_byte_set == last_byte_set) {
2734 // This sequence has only 7 bytes, compared to the 12 bytes below.
2735 Push(Immediate(0));
2736 movb(Operand(rsp, first_byte_set),
2737 Immediate(static_cast<int8_t>(smi >> (8 * first_byte_set))));
2738 return;
2739 }
2740 Register constant = GetSmiConstant(source);
2741 Push(constant);
2742}

2808void MacroAssembler::MovePair(Register dst0, Register src0, Register dst1,
2809 Register src1) {
2810 if (dst0 != src1) {
2811 // Normal case: Writing to dst0 does not destroy src1.
2812 Move(dst0, src0);
2813 Move(dst1, src1);
2814 } else if (dst1 != src0) {
2815 // Only dst0 and src1 are the same register,
2816 // but writing to dst1 does not destroy src0.
2817 Move(dst1, src1);
2818 Move(dst0, src0);
2819 } else {
2820 // dst0 == src1, and dst1 == src0, a swap is required:
2821 // dst0 \/ src0
2822 // dst1 /\ src1
2823 xchgq(dst0, dst1);
2824 }
2825}

2835
2836void MacroAssembler::Move(XMMRegister dst, uint32_t src) {
2837 if (src == 0) {
2838 Xorps(dst, dst);
2839 } else {
2840 unsigned nlz = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(src);
2841 unsigned ntz = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(src);
2842 unsigned pop = base::bits::CountPopulation(src);
2843 DCHECK_NE(0u, pop);
2844 if (pop + ntz + nlz == 32) {
2845 Pcmpeqd(dst, dst);
2846 if (ntz) Pslld(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(ntz + nlz));
2847 if (nlz) Psrld(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(nlz));
2848 } else {
2849 movl(kScratchRegister, Immediate(src));
2850 Movd(dst, kScratchRegister);
2851 }
2852 }
2853}
2854
2855void MacroAssembler::Move(XMMRegister dst, uint64_t src) {
2856 if (src == 0) {
2857 Xorpd(dst, dst);
2858 } else {
2859 unsigned nlz = base::bits::CountLeadingZeros(src);
2860 unsigned ntz = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(src);
2861 unsigned pop = base::bits::CountPopulation(src);
2862 DCHECK_NE(0u, pop);
2863 if (pop + ntz + nlz == 64) {
2864 Pcmpeqd(dst, dst);
2865 if (ntz) Psllq(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(ntz + nlz));
2866 if (nlz) Psrlq(dst, static_cast<uint8_t>(nlz));
2867 } else {
2868 uint32_t lower = static_cast<uint32_t>(src);
2869 uint32_t upper = static_cast<uint32_t>(src >> 32);
2870 if (upper == 0) {
2871 Move(dst, lower);
2872 } else {
2873 movq(kScratchRegister, src);
2874 Movq(dst, kScratchRegister);
2875 }
2876 }
2877 }
2878}
2879
2880void MacroAssembler::Move(XMMRegister dst, uint64_t high, uint64_t low) {
2881 if (high == low) {
2882 Move(dst, low);
2883 Punpcklqdq(dst, dst);
2884 return;
2885 }
2886
2887 Move(dst, low);
2888 movq(kScratchRegister, high);
2889 Pinsrq(dst, dst, kScratchRegister, uint8_t{1});
2890}

2963
2964void MacroAssembler::PushArray(Register array, Register size, Register scratch,
2965 PushArrayOrder order) {
2966 DCHECK(!AreAliased(array, size, scratch));
2967 Register counter = scratch;
2968 Label loop, entry;
2969 if (order == PushArrayOrder::kReverse) {
2970 Move(counter, 0);
2971 jmp(&entry);
2972 bind(&loop);
2973 Push(Operand(array, counter, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
2974 incq(counter);
2975 bind(&entry);
2976 cmpq(counter, size);
2977 j(less, &loop, Label::kNear);
2978 } else {
2979 movq(counter, size);
2980 jmp(&entry);
2981 bind(&loop);
2982 Push(Operand(array, counter, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
2983 bind(&entry);
2984 decq(counter);
2985 j(greater_equal, &loop, Label::kNear);
2986 }
2987}

2989void MacroAssembler::Move(Register result, Handle<HeapObject> object,
2990 RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
2991 // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
2992 // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
2993 // embedding the relocatable value.
2994 if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
2995 // TODO(v8:9706): Fix-it! This load will always uncompress the value
2996 // even when we are loading a compressed embedded object.
2997 IndirectLoadConstant(result, object);
2998 } else if (RelocInfo::IsCompressedEmbeddedObject(rmode)) {
2999 EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(object);
3000 DCHECK(is_uint32(index));
3001 movl(result, Immediate(static_cast<int>(index), rmode));
3002 } else {
3003 DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsFullEmbeddedObject(rmode));
3004 movq(result, Immediate64(object.address(), rmode));
3005 }
3006}

3170Operand MacroAssembler::EntryFromBuiltinIndexAsOperand(Register builtin_index) {
3171 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
3172 // The builtin_index register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
3173 Move(kScratchRegister, builtin_index); // Callee checks for equality.
3174 SmiUntagUnsigned(kScratchRegister);
3175 return Operand(kRootRegister, kScratchRegister, times_system_pointer_size,
3176 IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset());
3177 } else {
3178 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
3179
3180 // The builtin_index register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
3181 // Untagging is folded into the indexing operand below (we use
3182 // times_half_system_pointer_size since smis are already shifted by one).
3183 return Operand(kRootRegister, builtin_index, times_half_system_pointer_size,
3184 IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset());
3185 }

3192void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
3193 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("call", builtin));
3194 switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
3195 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute:
3196 Call(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET);
3197 break;
3198 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
3199 near_call(static_cast<intptr_t>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
3200 break;
3201 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect:
3202 Call(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
3203 break;
3204 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
3205 Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
3206 call(code, RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
3207 break;
3208 }
3209 }
3210}

3218 break;
3219 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
3220 near_jmp(static_cast<intptr_t>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
3221 break;
3222 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect:
3223 Jump(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
3224 break;
3225 case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
3226 Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);

3228 break;

3290void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
3291 uint16_t argument_count) {
3292#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3293 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
3294 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister == r15, "ABI mismatch");
3295 movl(r15, FieldOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
3296 LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(rcx, rbx, r15);
3297 // Force a safe crash if the parameter count doesn't match.
3298 cmpl(rbx, Immediate(argument_count));
3299 SbxCheck(less_equal, AbortReason::kJSSignatureMismatch);
3300 call(rcx);
3301#else
3302 CHECK(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
3303 LoadTaggedField(rcx, FieldOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
3304 CallCodeObject(rcx, kJSEntrypointTag);
3305#endif
3306}
3307
3308#if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
3309void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
3310 uint16_t argument_count) {
3311 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
3312 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister == r15, "ABI mismatch");
3313 movl(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister,
3314 Immediate(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
3315 // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
3316 // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the movl above (thus keeping the
3317 // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
3318 // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
3319 // invalidated by a compaction).
3320 // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
3321 static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
3322 LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(rcx, dispatch_handle);
3323 CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
3324 IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
3325 dispatch_handle));
3326 call(rcx);
3327}
3328#endif

3345
3346void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target,
3347 uint64_t signature_hash) {
3348 ExternalReference global_jump_table =
3349 ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
3350 Move(kScratchRegister, global_jump_table);
3351
3352#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
3353 Label fail, ok;
3354
3355 static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 16);
3356 shlq(target, Immediate(4));
3357
3358 cmpl(Operand(kScratchRegister, target, ScaleFactor::times_1,
3359 wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kOffsetOfSignatureHash),
3360 Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(signature_hash)));
3361 j(Condition::kNotEqual, &fail, Label::Distance::kNear);
3362
3363 cmpl(Operand(kScratchRegister, target, ScaleFactor::times_1,
3364 wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kOffsetOfSignatureHash + 4),
3365 Immediate(static_cast<int32_t>(signature_hash >> 32)));
3366 j(Condition::kNotEqual, &fail, Label::Distance::kNear);
3367 jmp(&ok, Label::Distance::kNear);
3368
3369 bind(&fail);
3370 Abort(AbortReason::kWasmSignatureMismatch);
3371
3372 bind(&ok);
3373 movq(target, Operand(kScratchRegister, target, ScaleFactor::times_1, 0));
3374#else
3375 static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 8);
3376 movq(target, Operand(kScratchRegister, target, ScaleFactor::times_8, 0));
3377#endif
3378}
3379
3380void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
3381 uint64_t signature_hash,
3382 CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
3383 ResolveWasmCodePointer(target, signature_hash);
3384 if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
3385 jmp(target);
3386 } else {
3387 call(target);
3388 }
3389}

3459void MacroAssembler::Lzcntl(Register dst, Register src) {
3460 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(LZCNT)) {
3461 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, LZCNT);
3462 lzcntl(dst, src);
3463 return;
3464 }

3466 bsrl(dst, src);
3467 j(not_zero, &not_zero_src, Label::kNear);
3468 Move(dst, 63); // 63^31 == 32
3469 bind(&not_zero_src);
3470 xorl(dst, Immediate(31)); // for x in [0..31], 31^x == 31 - x
3471}

3593 UNREACHABLE();
3594}

3596void MacroAssembler::Popcntq(Register dst, Operand src) {
3597 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(POPCNT)) {
3598 CpuFeatureScope scope(this, POPCNT);
3599 popcntq(dst, src);
3600 return;

3604
3605void MacroAssembler::PushStackHandler() {
3606 // Adjust this code if not the case.
3607 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
3608 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
3609
3610 Push(Immediate(0)); // Padding.
3611
3612 // Link the current handler as the next handler.
3613 ExternalReference handler_address =
3614 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate());
3615 Push(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(handler_address));
3616
3617 // Set this new handler as the current one.
3618 movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(handler_address), rsp);
3619}
3620
3621void MacroAssembler::PopStackHandler() {
3622 static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
3623 ExternalReference handler_address =
3624 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate());
3625 Pop(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(handler_address));
3626 addq(rsp, Immediate(StackHandlerConstants::kSize - kSystemPointerSize));
3627}
3628
3629void MacroAssembler::Ret() { ret(0); }
3630
3631void MacroAssembler::Ret(int bytes_dropped, Register scratch) {
3632 if (is_uint16(bytes_dropped)) {
3633 ret(bytes_dropped);
3634 } else {
3635 PopReturnAddressTo(scratch);
3636 addq(rsp, Immediate(bytes_dropped));
3637 PushReturnAddressFrom(scratch);
3638 ret(0);
3639 }
3640}

3642void MacroAssembler::IncsspqIfSupported(Register number_of_words,
3643 Register scratch) {
3644 // Optimized code can validate at runtime whether the cpu supports the
3645 // incsspq instruction, so it shouldn't use this method.
3646 CHECK(isolate()->IsGeneratingEmbeddedBuiltins());
3647 DCHECK_NE(number_of_words, scratch);
3648 Label not_supported;
3649 ExternalReference supports_cetss =
3650 ExternalReference::supports_cetss_address();
3651 Operand supports_cetss_operand =
3652 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(supports_cetss, scratch);
3653 cmpb(supports_cetss_operand, Immediate(0));
3654 j(equal, &not_supported, Label::kNear);
3655 incsspq(number_of_words);
3656 bind(&not_supported);
3657}

3707void MacroAssembler::JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(Register heap_object,
3708 Register scratch, Label* target,
3709 Label::Distance distance,
3710 Condition cc) {
3711 CHECK(cc == Condition::kUnsignedLessThan ||
3712 cc == Condition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual);
3713 if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
3714#ifdef DEBUG
3715 Label ok;
3716 LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
3717 CmpInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE,
3718 LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
3719 j(Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, &ok, Label::Distance::kNear);
3720 LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
3721 CmpInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE,
3722 LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE);
3723 j(Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, &ok, Label::Distance::kNear);
3724 Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidReceiver);
3725 bind(&ok);
3726#endif // DEBUG
3727
3728 // All primitive object's maps are allocated at the start of the read only
3729 // heap. Thus JS_RECEIVER's must have maps with larger (compressed)
3730 // addresses.
3731 LoadCompressedMap(scratch, heap_object);
3732 cmp_tagged(scratch, Immediate(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit));
3733 } else {
3734 static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
3735 CmpObjectType(heap_object, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, scratch);
3736 }
3737 j(cc, target, distance);
3738}

3759void MacroAssembler::TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(Register code) {
3760 const int kByteWithDeoptBitOffset = 0 * kByteSize;
3761 const int kByteWithDeoptBitOffsetInBits = kByteWithDeoptBitOffset * 8;
3762 static_assert(V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN == 1);
3763 static_assert(FIELD_SIZE(Code::kFlagsOffset) * kBitsPerByte == 32);
3764 static_assert(Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit >
3765 kByteWithDeoptBitOffsetInBits);

3767 Immediate(1 << (Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit -
3768 kByteWithDeoptBitOffsetInBits)));

3846void MacroAssembler::AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(

3952void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
3953 AbortReason abort_reason) {
3954 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
3955
3956 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3957 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp));
3958 Label ok;
3959
3960 Label::Distance dist = DEBUG_BOOL ? Label::kFar : Label::kNear;
3961
3962 JumpIfSmi(object, &ok, dist);
3963
3964 LoadMap(map_tmp, object);
3965 CmpInstanceType(map_tmp, LAST_NAME_TYPE);
3966 j(below_equal, &ok, dist);
3967
3968 CmpInstanceType(map_tmp, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
3969 j(above_equal, &ok, dist);
3970
3971 CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
3972 j(equal, &ok, dist);
3973
3974 CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
3975 j(equal, &ok, dist);
3976
3977 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
3978 j(equal, &ok, dist);
3979
3980 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
3981 j(equal, &ok, dist);
3982
3983 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
3984 j(equal, &ok, dist);
3985
3986 CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
3987 j(equal, &ok, dist);
3988
3989 Abort(abort_reason);
3990
3991 bind(&ok);
3992}

4010void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value) {
4011 DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
4012 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
4013 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4014 Operand counter_operand =
4015 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(ExternalReference::Create(counter));
4016 // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
4017 // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
4018 // field.
4019 if (value == 1) {
4020 incl(counter_operand);
4021 } else {
4022 addl(counter_operand, Immediate(value));
4023 }
4024 }
4025}

4044#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4045void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(
4046 Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
4047 InvokeType type, ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
4048 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4049 DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4050 LoadTaggedField(rsi, FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
4051 InvokeFunctionCode(rdi, new_target, actual_parameter_count, type,
4052 argument_adaption_mode);
4053}
4054
4055void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(
4056 Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
4057 InvokeType type, ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
4058 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4059 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
4060 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
4061 DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4062 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == rdx);
4063
4064 Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
4065 movl(dispatch_handle,
4066 FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
4067
4068 AssertFunction(function);
4069
4070 // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
4071 Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
4072 {
4073 ExternalReference debug_hook_active =
4074 ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate());
4075 Operand debug_hook_active_operand =
4076 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(debug_hook_active);
4077 cmpb(debug_hook_active_operand, Immediate(0));
4078 j(not_equal, &debug_hook);
4079 }
4080 bind(&continue_after_hook);
4081
4082 // Clear the new.target register if not given.
4083 if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
4084 LoadRoot(rdx, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4085 }
4086
4087 if (argument_adaption_mode == ArgumentAdaptionMode::kAdapt) {
4088 Register expected_parameter_count = rbx;
4089 LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(expected_parameter_count,
4090 dispatch_handle);
4091 InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
4092 }
4093
4094 // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
4095 // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
4096 // call sites.
4097 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
4098 LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(rcx, dispatch_handle);
4099 switch (type) {
4100 case InvokeType::kCall:
4101 call(rcx);
4102 break;
4103 case InvokeType::kJump:
4104 jmp(rcx);
4105 break;
4106 }
4107 Label done;
4108 jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
4109
4110 // Deferred debug hook.
4111 bind(&debug_hook);
4112 CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, dispatch_handle,
4113 actual_parameter_count);
4114 jmp(&continue_after_hook);
4115
4116 bind(&done);
4117}
4118#else
4119void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function, Register new_target,
4120 Register actual_parameter_count,
4121 InvokeType type) {
4122 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4123 LoadTaggedField(
4124 rbx, FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
4125 movzxwq(rbx,
4126 FieldOperand(rbx, SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
4127
4128 InvokeFunction(function, new_target, rbx, actual_parameter_count, type);
4129}

4131void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function, Register new_target,
4132 Register expected_parameter_count,
4133 Register actual_parameter_count,
4134 InvokeType type) {
4135 DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4136 LoadTaggedField(rsi, FieldOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
4137 InvokeFunctionCode(rdi, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
4138 actual_parameter_count, type);
4139}
4140
4141void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
4142 Register expected_parameter_count,
4143 Register actual_parameter_count,
4144 InvokeType type) {
4145 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4146 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
4147 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
4148 DCHECK_EQ(function, rdi);
4149 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == rdx);
4150
4151 AssertFunction(function);
4152
4153 // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
4154 Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
4155 {
4156 ExternalReference debug_hook_active =
4157 ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate());
4158 Operand debug_hook_active_operand =
4159 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(debug_hook_active);
4160 cmpb(debug_hook_active_operand, Immediate(0));
4161 j(not_equal, &debug_hook);
4162 }
4163 bind(&continue_after_hook);
4164
4165 // Clear the new.target register if not given.
4166 if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
4167 LoadRoot(rdx, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4168 }
4169
4170 Label done;
4171 InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
4172 // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
4173 // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
4174 // call sites.
4175 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == rcx, "ABI mismatch");
4176 constexpr int unused_argument_count = 0;
4177 switch (type) {
4178 case InvokeType::kCall:
4179 CallJSFunction(function, unused_argument_count);
4180 break;
4181 case InvokeType::kJump:
4182 JumpJSFunction(function);
4183 break;
4184 }
4185 jmp(&done, Label::kNear);
4186
4187 // Deferred debug hook.
4188 bind(&debug_hook);
4189 CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
4190 actual_parameter_count);
4191 jmp(&continue_after_hook);
4192
4193 bind(&done);
4194}
4195#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4196
4197Operand MacroAssembler::StackLimitAsOperand(StackLimitKind kind) {
4198 DCHECK(root_array_available());
4199 intptr_t offset = kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
4200 ? IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset()
4201 : IsolateData::jslimit_offset();
4202
4203 CHECK(is_int32(offset));
4204 return Operand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4205}
4206
4207void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(
4208 Register num_args, Label* stack_overflow,
4209 Label::Distance stack_overflow_distance) {
4210 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4211 DCHECK_NE(num_args, kScratchRegister);
4212 // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
4213 // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
4214 // limit" is checked.
4215 movq(kScratchRegister, rsp);
4216 // Make kScratchRegister the space we have left. The stack might already be
4217 // overflowed here which will cause kScratchRegister to become negative.
4218 subq(kScratchRegister, StackLimitAsOperand(StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit));
4219 // TODO(victorgomes): Use ia32 approach with leaq, since it requires less
4220 // instructions.
4221 sarq(kScratchRegister, Immediate(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4222 // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
4223 cmpq(kScratchRegister, num_args);
4224 // Signed comparison.
4225 // TODO(victorgomes): Save some bytes in the builtins that use stack checks
4226 // by jumping to a builtin that throws the exception.
4227 j(less_equal, stack_overflow, stack_overflow_distance);
4228}
4229
4230void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
4231 Register actual_parameter_count,
4232 InvokeType type) {
4233 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4234 if (expected_parameter_count == actual_parameter_count) {
4235 Move(rax, actual_parameter_count);
4236 return;
4237 }
4238 Label regular_invoke;
4239
4240 // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
4241 // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
4242 subq(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count);
4243 j(less_equal, &regular_invoke, Label::kFar);
4244
4245 Label stack_overflow;
4246 StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, &stack_overflow);
4247
4248 // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
4249 // receiver and the return address.
4250 {
4251 Label copy, check;
4252 Register src = r8, dest = rsp, num = r9, current = r11;
4253 movq(src, rsp);
4254 leaq(kScratchRegister,
4255 Operand(expected_parameter_count, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
4256 AllocateStackSpace(kScratchRegister);
4257 // Extra words are for the return address (if a jump).
4258 int extra_words =
4259 type == InvokeType::kCall ? 0 : kReturnAddressStackSlotCount;
4260
4261 leaq(num, Operand(rax, extra_words)); // Number of words to copy.
4262 Move(current, 0);
4263 // Fall-through to the loop body because there are non-zero words to copy.
4264 bind(&copy);
4265 movq(kScratchRegister,
4266 Operand(src, current, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
4267 movq(Operand(dest, current, times_system_pointer_size, 0),
4268 kScratchRegister);
4269 incq(current);
4270 bind(&check);
4271 cmpq(current, num);
4272 j(less, &copy);
4273 leaq(r8, Operand(rsp, num, times_system_pointer_size, 0));
4274 }
4275 // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
4276 LoadRoot(kScratchRegister, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4277 {
4278 Label loop;
4279 bind(&loop);
4280 decq(expected_parameter_count);
4281 movq(Operand(r8, expected_parameter_count, times_system_pointer_size, 0),
4282 kScratchRegister);
4283 j(greater, &loop, Label::kNear);
4284 }
4285 jmp(&regular_invoke);
4286
4287 bind(&stack_overflow);
4288 {
4289 FrameScope frame(
4290 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
4291 CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
4292 int3(); // This should be unreachable.
4293 }
4294 bind(&regular_invoke);
4295}

4297void MacroAssembler::CallDebugOnFunctionCall(
4298 Register fun, Register new_target,
4299 Register expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
4300 Register actual_parameter_count) {
4301 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4302 // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
4303 // Receiver is located on top of the stack if we have a frame (usually a
4304 // construct frame), or after the return address if we do not yet have a
4305 // frame.
4306 movq(kScratchRegister, Operand(rsp, has_frame() ? 0 : kSystemPointerSize));
4307
4308 FrameScope frame(
4309 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
4310
4311 SmiTag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4312 Push(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4313
4314 SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
4315 Push(actual_parameter_count);
4316 SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
4317
4318 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
4319 Push(new_target);
4320 }
4321 Push(fun);
4322 Push(fun);
4323 Push(kScratchRegister);
4324 CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
4325 Pop(fun);
4326 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
4327 Pop(new_target);
4328 }
4329 Pop(actual_parameter_count);
4330 SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
4331 Pop(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4332 SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
4333}

4379#if defined(V8_TARGET_OS_WIN) || defined(V8_TARGET_OS_MACOS)
4380void MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace(Register bytes_scratch) {
4381 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4382 // On Windows and on macOS, we cannot increment the stack size by more than
4383 // one page (minimum page size is 4KB) without accessing at least one byte on
4384 // the page. Check this:
4385 // https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa227153(v=vs.60).aspx.
4386 Label check_offset;
4387 Label touch_next_page;
4388 jmp(&check_offset);
4389 bind(&touch_next_page);
4390 subq(rsp, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4391 // Just to touch the page, before we increment further.
4392 movb(Operand(rsp, 0), Immediate(0));
4393 subq(bytes_scratch, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4394
4395 bind(&check_offset);
4396 cmpq(bytes_scratch, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4397 j(greater_equal, &touch_next_page);
4398
4399 subq(rsp, bytes_scratch);
4400}
4401
4402void MacroAssembler::AllocateStackSpace(int bytes) {
4403 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4404 DCHECK_GE(bytes, 0);
4405 while (bytes >= kStackPageSize) {
4406 subq(rsp, Immediate(kStackPageSize));
4407 movb(Operand(rsp, 0), Immediate(0));
4408 bytes -= kStackPageSize;
4409 }
4410 if (bytes == 0) return;
4411 subq(rsp, Immediate(bytes));
4412}
4413#endif
