4415void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(int extra_slots,
4416 StackFrame::Type frame_type,
4417 Register c_function) {
4418 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4419 DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
4420 frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
4421 frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
4422 frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
4423
4424 // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
4425 // All constants are relative to the frame pointer of the exit frame.
4426 DCHECK_EQ(kFPOnStackSize + kPCOnStackSize,
4427 ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
4428 DCHECK_EQ(kFPOnStackSize, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
4429 DCHECK_EQ(0 * kSystemPointerSize, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
4430 pushq(rbp);
4431 movq(rbp, rsp);
4432
4433 Push(Immediate(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
4434 DCHECK_EQ(-2 * kSystemPointerSize, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset);
4435 Push(Immediate(0)); // Saved entry sp, patched below.
4436
4437 DCHECK(!AreAliased(rbp, kContextRegister, c_function));
4438 using ER = ExternalReference;
4439 Store(ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate()), rbp);
4440 Store(ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate()),
4441 kContextRegister);
4442 Store(ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCFunctionAddress, isolate()), c_function);
4443
4444#ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
4445 // Note this is only correct under the assumption that the caller hasn't
4446 // considered home stack slots already.
4447 // TODO(jgruber): This is a bit hacky since the caller in most cases still
4448 // needs to know about the home stack slots in order to address reserved
4449 // slots. Consider moving this fully into caller code.
4450 extra_slots += kWindowsHomeStackSlots;
4451#endif
4452 AllocateStackSpace(extra_slots * kSystemPointerSize);
4453
4454 AlignStackPointer();
4455
4456 // Patch the saved entry sp.
4457 movq(Operand(rbp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset), rsp);
4458}

4460void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame() {
4461 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4462
4463 leave();
4464
4465 // Restore the current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
4466 ExternalReference context_address =
4467 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
4468 Operand context_operand = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address);
4469 movq(rsi, context_operand);
4470#ifdef DEBUG
4471 Move(context_operand, Context::kInvalidContext);
4472#endif
4473
4474 // Clear the top frame.
4475 ExternalReference c_entry_fp_address =
4476 ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
4477 Operand c_entry_fp_operand = ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address);
4478 Move(c_entry_fp_operand, 0);
4479}

4492void MacroAssembler::TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(Register scratch_and_result,
4493 CodeKind min_opt_level,
4494 Register feedback_vector,
4495 FeedbackSlot slot,
4496 Label* on_result,
4497 Label::Distance distance) {
4498 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4499 Label fallthrough, on_mark_deopt;
4500 LoadTaggedField(
4501 scratch_and_result,
4502 FieldOperand(feedback_vector,
4503 FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
4504 LoadWeakValue(scratch_and_result, &fallthrough);
4505
4506 // Is it marked_for_deoptimization? If yes, clear the slot.
4507 {
4508 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
4509 LoadCodePointerField(
4510 scratch_and_result,
4511 FieldOperand(scratch_and_result, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset),
4512 kScratchRegister);
4513
4514 TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch_and_result);
4515
4516 if (min_opt_level == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
4517 j(not_zero, &on_mark_deopt, Label::Distance::kNear);
4518
4519 TestCodeIsTurbofanned(scratch_and_result);
4520 j(not_zero, on_result, distance);
4521 jmp(&fallthrough);
4522 } else {
4523 DCHECK_EQ(min_opt_level, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
4524 j(equal, on_result, distance);
4525 }
4526
4527 bind(&on_mark_deopt);
4528 StoreTaggedField(
4529 FieldOperand(feedback_vector,
4530 FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())),
4531 ClearedValue());
4532 }
4533
4534 bind(&fallthrough);
4535 Move(scratch_and_result, 0);
4536}

4547void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_arguments) {
4548 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4549 int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
4550 DCHECK_NE(frame_alignment, 0);
4551 DCHECK_GE(num_arguments, 0);
4552
4553 // Make stack end at alignment and allocate space for arguments and old rsp.
4554 movq(kScratchRegister, rsp);
4555 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
4556 int argument_slots_on_stack =
4557 ArgumentStackSlotsForCFunctionCall(num_arguments);
4558 AllocateStackSpace((argument_slots_on_stack + 1) * kSystemPointerSize);
4559 andq(rsp, Immediate(-frame_alignment));
4560 movq(Operand(rsp, argument_slots_on_stack * kSystemPointerSize),
4561 kScratchRegister);
4562}

4564int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function, int num_arguments,
4565 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
4566 Label* return_location) {
4567 // Note: The "CallCFunction" code comment will be generated by the other
4568 // CallCFunction method called below.
4569 LoadAddress(rax, function);
4570 return CallCFunction(rax, num_arguments, set_isolate_data_slots,
4571 return_location);
4572}
4573
4574int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_arguments,
4575 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
4576 Label* return_location) {
4577 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4578 DCHECK_LE(num_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
4579 DCHECK(has_frame());
4580 // Check stack alignment.
4581 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4582 CheckStackAlignment();
4583 }
4584
4585 // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains iterable,
4586 // even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS and C frames.
4587 Label get_pc;
4588
4589 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
4590 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kScratchRegister, function));
4591 leaq(kScratchRegister, Operand(&get_pc, 0));
4592
4593 CHECK(root_array_available());
4594 movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC),
4595 kScratchRegister);
4596 movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP), rbp);
4597 }
4598
4599 call(function);
4600 int call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
4601 bind(&get_pc);
4602 if (return_location) bind(return_location);
4603
4604 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
4605 // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
4606 movq(ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP),
4607 Immediate(0));
4608 }
4609
4610 DCHECK_NE(base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment(), 0);
4611 DCHECK_GE(num_arguments, 0);
4612 int argument_slots_on_stack =
4613 ArgumentStackSlotsForCFunctionCall(num_arguments);
4614 movq(rsp, Operand(rsp, argument_slots_on_stack * kSystemPointerSize));
4615
4616 return call_pc_offset;
4617}

4619void MacroAssembler::MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(Register object,
4620 Register header) {
4621 constexpr intptr_t alignment_mask =
4622 MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler();
4623 if (header == object) {
4624 andq(header, Immediate(~alignment_mask));
4625 } else {
4626 movq(header, Immediate(~alignment_mask));
4627 andq(header, object);
4628 }

4631void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, Register scratch, int mask,
4632 Condition cc, Label* condition_met,
4633 Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
4634 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4635 DCHECK(cc == zero || cc == not_zero);
4636 MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(object, scratch);
4637 if (mask < (1 << kBitsPerByte)) {
4638 testb(Operand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()),
4639 Immediate(static_cast<uint8_t>(mask)));
4640 } else {
4641 testl(Operand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()), Immediate(mask));
4642 }
4643 j(cc, condition_met, condition_met_distance);
4644}

4659
4660void MacroAssembler::CheckMarkBit(Register object, Register scratch0,
4661 Register scratch1, Condition cc,
4662 Label* condition_met,
4663 Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
4664 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4665 DCHECK(cc == carry || cc == not_carry);
4666 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, scratch0, scratch1));
4667
4668 // Computing cell.
4669 MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(object, scratch0);
4670#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4671 movl(scratch0, Operand(scratch0, MemoryChunk::MetadataIndexOffset()));
4672 andl(scratch0,
4673 Immediate(MemoryChunkConstants::kMetadataPointerTableSizeMask));
4674 shll(scratch0, Immediate(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
4675 LoadAddress(scratch1,
4676 ExternalReference::memory_chunk_metadata_table_address());
4677 movq(scratch0, Operand(scratch1, scratch0, times_1, 0));
4678#else // !V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4679 movq(scratch0, Operand(scratch0, MemoryChunk::MetadataOffset()));
4680#endif // !V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
4681 if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
4682 Push(object);
4683 movq(scratch1, Operand(scratch0, MemoryChunkMetadata::AreaStartOffset()));
4684 MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(scratch1, scratch1);
4685 MemoryChunkHeaderFromObject(object, object);
4686 cmpq(object, scratch1);
4687 Check(equal, AbortReason::kMetadataAreaStartDoesNotMatch);
4688 Pop(object);
4689 }
4690 addq(scratch0, Immediate(MutablePageMetadata::MarkingBitmapOffset()));
4691
4692 movq(scratch1, object);
4693 andq(scratch1, Immediate(MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
4694 // It's important not to fold the next two shifts.
4695 shrq(scratch1, Immediate(kTaggedSizeLog2 + MarkingBitmap::kBitsPerCellLog2));
4696 shlq(scratch1, Immediate(kBitsPerByteLog2));
4697 addq(scratch0, scratch1);
4698
4699 // Computing mask.
4700 movq(scratch1, object);
4701 andq(scratch1, Immediate(MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
4702 shrq(scratch1, Immediate(kTaggedSizeLog2));
4703 andq(scratch1, Immediate(MarkingBitmap::kBitIndexMask));
4704 btq(Operand(scratch0, 0), scratch1);
4705
4706 j(cc, condition_met, condition_met_distance);
4707}

4709void MacroAssembler::ComputeCodeStartAddress(Register dst) {
4710 Label current;
4711 bind(&current);
4712 int pc = pc_offset();
4713 // Load effective address to get the address of the current instruction.
4714 leaq(dst, Operand(&current, -pc));
4715}

4717// Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
4718// jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
4719// to:
4720// 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
4721// the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
4722// 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
4723// 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
4724//
4725// Note: With leaptiering we simply assert the code is not deoptimized.
4726void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized(Register scratch) {
4727 int offset = InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
4728 if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
4729 LoadProtectedPointerField(
4730 scratch, Operand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
4731 TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch);
4732 }
4733#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4734 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
4735 Assert(zero, AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
4736 }
4737#else
4738 TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, not_zero);
4739#endif
4740}

4742void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
4743 DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
4744 Label*) {
4745 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4746 // Note: Assembler::call is used here on purpose to guarantee fixed-size
4747 // exits even on Atom CPUs; see MacroAssembler::Call for Atom-specific
4748 // performance tuning which emits a different instruction sequence.
4749 call(EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(target));
4750 DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
4751 (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
4752 : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
4753}
4754
4755void MacroAssembler::Trap() { int3(); }
4756void MacroAssembler::DebugBreak() { int3(); }
4757
4758// Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
4759// from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
4760// and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
4761// (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
4762// (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
4763// allocated for the fast call).
4764void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
4765 Register function_address,
4766 ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
4767 int slots_to_drop_on_return,
4768 MemOperand* argc_operand,
4769 MemOperand return_value_operand) {
4770 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
4771 Label propagate_exception;
4772 Label delete_allocated_handles;
4773 Label leave_exit_frame;
4774
4775 using ER = ExternalReference;
4776
4777 Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
4778 MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4779 ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
4780 MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4781 ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
4782 MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4783 ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
4784
4785 Register return_value = rax;
4786 Register scratch = kCArgRegs[3];
4787
4788 // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
4789 // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
4790 // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
4791 Register prev_next_address_reg = r12;
4792 Register prev_limit_reg = r15;
4793
4794 // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
4795 // this function must not corrupt them. kScratchRegister might be used
4796 // implicitly by the macro assembler.
4797 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
4798 return_value, scratch, kScratchRegister,
4799 prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
4800 // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
4801 // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
4802 // fine).
4803 DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
4804 scratch, kScratchRegister, prev_next_address_reg,
4805 prev_limit_reg));
4806 DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
4807 scratch, kScratchRegister, prev_next_address_reg,
4808 prev_limit_reg));
4809 {
4810 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
4811 "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
4812 __ movq(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
4813 __ movq(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
4814 __ addl(level_mem_op, Immediate(1));
4815 }
4816
4817 Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
4818 if (with_profiling) {
4819 __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
4820 __ cmpb(__ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode),
4821 Immediate(0));
4822 __ j(not_zero, &profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
4823#ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
4824 __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
4825 __ Move(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
4826 __ cmpl(Operand(scratch, 0), Immediate(0));
4827 __ j(not_zero, &profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
4828#endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
4829 }
4830
4831 __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
4832 __ call(function_address);
4833 __ bind(&done_api_call);
4834
4835 __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
4836 __ movq(return_value, return_value_operand);
4837
4838 {
4839 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
4840 masm,
4841 "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
4842 "Restore previous handle scope.");
4843 __ subl(level_mem_op, Immediate(1));
4844 __ Assert(above_equal, AbortReason::kInvalidHandleScopeLevel);
4845 __ movq(next_mem_op, prev_next_address_reg);
4846 __ cmpq(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
4847 __ j(not_equal, &delete_allocated_handles);
4848 }
4849
4850 __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
4851 __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
4852
4853 Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
4854 if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
4855 __ movq(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
4856 }
4857 __ LeaveExitFrame();
4858
4859 {
4860 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
4861 "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
4862 __ CompareRoot(
4863 __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg),
4864 RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
4865 __ j(not_equal, &propagate_exception);
4866 }
4867
4868 __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch,
4869 AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
4870
4871 if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
4872 DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
4873 __ ret(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize);
4874 } else {
4875 __ PopReturnAddressTo(scratch);
4876 // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
4877 __ leaq(rsp, Operand(rsp, argc_reg, times_system_pointer_size,
4878 slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
4879 // Push and ret (instead of jmp) to keep the RSB and the CET shadow stack
4880 // balanced.
4881 __ PushReturnAddressFrom(scratch);
4882 __ ret(0);
4883 }
4884 if (with_profiling) {
4885 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
4886 // Call the api function via thunk wrapper.
4887 __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
4888 // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
4889 if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
4890 MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4891 IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
4892 __ movq(thunk_arg_mem_op, thunk_arg);
4893 }
4894 __ Call(thunk_ref);
4895 __ jmp(&done_api_call);
4896 }
4897 __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
4898 __ bind(&propagate_exception);
4899 __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
4900 {
4901 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
4902 masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
4903 __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
4904 __ movq(limit_mem_op, prev_limit_reg);
4905 // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
4906 Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
4907 __ movq(saved_result, return_value);
4908 __ LoadAddress(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
4909 __ Call(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions());
4910 __ movq(return_value, saved_result);
4911 __ jmp(&leave_exit_frame);
4912 }
4913}
4914
4915} // namespace internal
4916} // namespace v8
4917
4918#undef __
4919
4920#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_X64
